dden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Mai 15, 2026</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eei1704363244858.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eei1704363244858.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eei1704363244858.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cdt1665702793781\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"cdt1665702793781__relationships_35565\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A relationship is an association between one entity and another. It is modeled as a\n      development object belonging to the many-side entity in a one-to-many relationship. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cdt1665702793781__p_d10244e1_d10245e1_d10246e1\">The Relationship object specifies the primary or candidate keys to be used in maintaining the association, as well as the delete constraints to be used when deleting occurrences in the related entities.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cdt1665702793781__p_d10247e1_d10248e1_d10249e1\">Uniface supports one-to-many relationships and uses these as the basis for modeling one-to-one and many-to-many relationships.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cdt1665702793781__p_d10250e1_d10251e1_d10252e1\">One-to-one relationships can be defined by a one-to-many relationship in which the foreign key in the many entity is a candidate key.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cdt1665702793781__p_d10253e1_d10254e1_d10255e1\">Many-to-many relationships must be implemented by creating an intermediate entity. For example, an employee can be assigned to multiple projects and a project can involve many employees. In the following illustration, the Employment entity handles the many-to-many relationship between an employee and projects.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"cdt1665702793781__fig_d10256e1_d10257e1_d10258e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Modeling Many-to-Many Associations</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Model for many-to-many relationships\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/datamodel.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 1. Modeling Many-to-Many Associations\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/datamodel.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnf1665702703926.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Referential Integrity</a><p>Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5752985\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5752985\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Relationships Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Mai 15, 2026 Summarize Uniface 10.4 A relationship is an association between one entity and another. It is modeled as a development object belonging to the many-side entity in a one-to-many relationship. The Relationship object specifies the primary or candidate keys to be used in maintaining the association, as well as the delete constraints to be used when deleting occurrences in the related entities. Uniface supports one-to-many relationships and uses these as the basis for modeling one-to-one and many-to-many relationships. One-to-one relationships can be defined by a one-to-many relationship in which the foreign key in the many entity is a candidate key. Many-to-many relationships must be implemented by creating an intermediate entity. For example, an employee can be assigned to multiple projects and a project can involve many employees. In the following illustration, the Employment entity handles the many-to-many relationship between an employee and projects. Figure 1. Modeling Many-to-Many Associations Related Links Referential Integrity Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}